Answer: The issue is that you are not moving the cursor to the next position after each iteration. You are calling moveToNext() before checking if there is a next position. Therefore, you are always on the same position.

You should move to the next position after you have retrieved the values.

Here is the corrected code:

public void loadTrack() {
    SQLiteDatabase db1 = waypoints.getWritableDatabase();
    Cursor trackCursor = db1.query(TABLE_NAME, FROM, "trackidfk=1", null, null, null, ORDER_BY);

    trackCursor.moveToFirst();
    while (!trackCursor.isAfterLast()) {
        Double lat = trackCursor.getDouble(2);
        Double lon = trackCursor.getDouble(1);
        //overlay.addGeoPoint( new GeoPoint( (int)(lat*1E6),  (int)(lon*1E6)));
        System.out.println(lon);
        System.out.println(lat);

        trackCursor.moveToNext();
    }
}

This will move the cursor to the next position after each iteration, so you will get all the values.

Also, you should check if the cursor is after the last position using isAfterLast() instead of moveToNext() because moveToNext() will return false if there is no next position.

I hope this helps.

